Armstrong Bakam, Bauchi The Bauchi State Government has proposed a budget of N213 billion for the 2021 fiscal year. The state Commissioner of Budget and Economic Planning, Dr. Aminu Gamawa, disclosed this while briefing journalists on the outcome of the State Executive Council Meeting presided over by the State Governor, Bala Mohammed, on Tuesday. He said that the budget christened, “Budget of Consolidation” comprises N120 billion Capital Expenditure and a Recurrent Expenditure of N93.1 billion. According to him, the Capital Expenditure consists of 56 per cent while the Recurrent Expenditure is 44 percent. He said that the budget which will soon be sent to the State Assembly for consideration, will focus on four key areas namely: Administration, Economy, Law and Justice and the Social Sector. Gamawa said in the education sector, one Secondary School along with a staff quarters will be renovated in each Local Government Areas of the state. Copyright PUNCH.
